President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed June 2018 as National Homeownership Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of homeownership in achieving the American Dream and financial security. The President emphasizes the positive impact of his administration's economic policies, including tax cuts and deregulation, which have led to economic growth, low unemployment rates, and increased opportunities for Americans to own homes. He also mentions the benefits of homeownership, such as providing a sense of pride, stability, and a place to raise families. The President commends those Americans who have achieved homeownership and views their success as an inspiration for others pursuing their own American Dream.